of drain cleaner by mistake.

6
00:00:31,197 --> 00:00:33,117
{\an8}I heard she fell down
a well.

7
00:00:33,199 --> 00:00:34,159
{\an8}Ahh!

8
00:00:34,242 --> 00:00:36,372
{\an8}-(sobbing)
-Come on, now.

9
00:00:36,453 --> 00:00:38,713
{\an8}My God,
she's been dumped again.

10
00:00:38,788 --> 00:00:40,828
{\an8}Children,
I won't be staying long.

11
00:00:40,915 --> 00:00:43,995
{\an8}I just came from the doctor,
and I have lyme disease.

12
00:00:44,085 --> 00:00:45,745
{\an8}Principal Skinner
will run the class

13
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:47,547
{\an8}until a substitute arrives.

14
00:00:47,630 --> 00:00:49,720
{\an8}-What's lyme disease?
-I'll field that one.

15
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:53,139
{\an8}Lyme disease is spread
by small parasites called ticks.

16
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:55,219
{\an8}When a diseased tick
attaches itself to you

17
00:00:55,305 --> 00:00:56,715
{\an8}-and begins sucking your blood,
-Ohh.

18
00:00:56,806 --> 00:00:58,766
{\an8}malignant spirochetes
infest your bloodstream,

19
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:01,690
{\an8}eventually spreading to your
spinal fluid and on into the brain.

20
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:03,060
{\an8}The brain.
Oh, dear God.

21
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:04,686
{\an8}(class chatters)

22
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:07,033
{\an8}Come on, Elizabeth.
Come, come.

23
00:01:07,108 --> 00:01:09,608
{\an8}Well now, children,
here we are.

24
00:01:09,694 --> 00:01:11,994
Open your primers to page 32.

25
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:13,362
Ah, subtraction.

26
00:01:13,448 --> 00:01:15,618
(screaming from above)

27
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:18,290
Bart Simpson!
I know it's you.

28
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:23,120
And here comes snowball two.
This is the one we kept.

29
00:01:23,208 --> 00:01:24,708
KIDS:
Eww!

30
00:01:24,793 --> 00:01:25,843
We were gonna keep the gray one,
but the mother ate her.

31
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,459
KIDS:
Eww!

32
00:01:27,545 --> 00:01:28,835
Mrs. Krabappel,

33
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,722
he's traumatizing
the children.

34
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:32,379
As usual,
I agree with you, Martin.

35
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:34,137
Bart, shut that off
and take your seat immediately.

36
00:01:34,219 --> 00:01:35,719
Oh look, this is really cool.

37
00:01:35,804 --> 00:01:38,144
