-Are you the substitute?
-Yes, sir.

43
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:57,697
-Yes, I am.
-Are you insane?

44
00:01:57,784 --> 00:01:59,744
No sir, no I'm not.
It's my way of getting their attention.

45
00:01:59,828 --> 00:02:02,208
Well, all right.
Uh, play friendly

46
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:04,418
with your new teacher,
children.

47
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:07,879
Howdy. I am a Texas cowboy.
The year is 1830.

48
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:09,671
You young'uns ask me
any questions you like.

49
00:02:09,754 --> 00:02:12,384
Can we play kickball instead
of science after lunch?

50
00:02:12,465 --> 00:02:15,425
Kickball? Son, there ain't
no kickball in 1830.

51
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:17,720
Any other questions?

52
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:19,644
Shoot, it's awfully quiet
on the plains here.

53
00:02:19,722 --> 00:02:22,272
Well, how about this? Everybody?
I want to see two eyes

54
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:24,810
on every single person
staring right at me right now.

55
00:02:24,894 --> 00:02:26,984
There are three things wrong
with my costume.

56
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:31,033
Anybody names those three
things will get my hat.

57
00:02:31,109 --> 00:02:32,689
I believe I know the answer.

58
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:35,317
-What's your name?
-Lisa Simpson.

59
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:37,485
-Well, go ahead, Miss Simpson.
-Um, one.

60
00:02:37,574 --> 00:02:39,584
Your belt buckle says
"State of Texas,"

61
