of the overlords of the genre:

83
00:03:29,959 --> 00:03:32,709
Asimov, Bester, Clarke...

84
00:03:32,795 --> 00:03:35,085
-What about Ray Bradbury?
-I'm aware of his work.

85
00:03:35,173 --> 00:03:40,013
Thank you,
and keep watching the skies!

86
00:03:40,094 --> 00:03:42,974
Excellent! Excellent! Martin!

87
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:44,886
If you're through
with your pemmican,

88
00:03:44,974 --> 00:03:48,104
why don't we sing a song
about cowboys?

89
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:49,686
Now, this one's not
very accurate,

90
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:52,071
but we can fix it up
as we go along. Okay?

91
00:03:52,148 --> 00:03:56,988
<i>♪ Home,</i>
<i>home on the range ♪</i>

92
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,160
(quietly) Actually, the range
was far from home.

93
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:00,659
It was a very desolate place

94
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:03,330
where danger and disease
rode tall in the saddle.

95
00:04:03,409 --> 00:04:08,709
<i>♪ Where the deer</i>
<i>and the antelope play ♪</i>

96
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,830
(whispering) But unlike
the efficient Indians,

97
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:12,707
cowboys used only the tongue
of the antelope,

98
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:14,344
and they threw the rest away.

99
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:17,380
<i>♪ Where seldom is heard ♪</i>

100
00:04:17,465 --> 00:04:20,635
<i>-♪ A discouraging word ♪</i>
- (giggling)

101
00:04:20,718 --> 00:04:26,558
{\an8}<i>♪ And the skies are</i>
<i>not cloudy all day. ♪</i>

102
00:04:26,641 --> 00:04:29,851
Hey, what's this?
Did you do it?

103
00:04:29,936 --> 00:04:32,306
No, it wasn't me. I would never do
anything like that.

104
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:34,567
It was just one of those immature people
who, instead of building themselves up--

105
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:36,319
It's neat.
Can I have it?

106
00:04:36,401 --> 00:04:37,741
Yes, but I didn't do it.

107
00:04:37,819 --> 00:04:39,399
Are you sure you didn't?
It's good.

108
00:04:39,487 --> 00:04:41,907
No, but I'm starting
to wish I had.

109
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:43,910
(chuckles) Ladies and gentlemen:
The Singing Dork.

110
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:47,162
(whispering)
Lisa.

111
00:04:47,245 --> 00:04:49,455
(snickering)

112
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:50,749
Any other nominations?

113
00:04:50,832 --> 00:04:52,712
TOGETHER:
We nominate Bart Simpson.

114
00:04:52,792 --> 00:04:54,592
Speech! Speech!

115
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:56,589
I had a speech ready,
but my dog ate it.

116
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:58,421
-(kids laughing)
-Children!

117
00:04:58,506 --> 00:05:01,256
Good. Bart, I need
someone very reliable

118
00:05:01,342 --> 00:05:04,472
