00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:30,502
"Here is a drawing
of a spirochete.

242
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:33,048
-Love, Ralph."
-Oh, that's great, Ralph.

243
00:10:33,132 --> 00:10:34,802
-(bell ringing)
-Hey, kids!

244
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:36,264
I've learned
that in two weeks,

245
00:10:36,344 --> 00:10:37,854
the Springfield
Museum of Natural History

246
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:41,308
will be closing forever
due to a lack of interest.

247
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,930
I urge you to see it
while you can.

248
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:45,348
(slurping)

249
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:49,356
Hmm. Lisa needs to go
to the museum tomorrow,

250
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,230
and I think
you should take her.

251
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:53,317
-The museum? Tomorrow?
-Mm-hmm.

252
00:10:53,402 --> 00:10:57,452
Oh, Marge, I'd love to,
but I was planning on...

253
00:10:57,531 --> 00:10:59,831
(thinking) <i>Sleeping?</i>
<i>Eating a big sandwich?</i>

254
00:10:59,909 --> 00:11:02,329
<i>Watching TV?</i>
<i>Spending time with the boy!</i>

255
00:11:02,411 --> 00:11:04,791
Spending time with the boy.
The boy needs attention, Marge.

256
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:06,792
Homer, I've been talking
to Lisa,

257
00:11:06,874 --> 00:11:08,214
and I'm concerned about
your relationship with her.

258
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:09,672
Me, too, Mom.

259
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:11,342
-I think they're drifting apart.
-Shut up, boy.

260
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:14,300
-Homer, please!
-Marge, you don't understand.

261
00:11:14,382 --> 00:11:16,682
I can't do it because--
<i>You're trapped.</i>

262
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:18,469
<i>If you were smarter,</i>
<i>you might think of something.</i>

263
00:11:18,552 --> 00:11:20,602
<i>But you're not.</i>
<i>So you just might as well--</i>

264
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,720
All right, all right,
I'll take her.

265
00:11:22,807 --> 00:11:25,387
Lousy brain.

266
00:11:25,476 --> 00:11:29,766
Hey, what do you mean
by "suggested donation"?

267
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:31,565
Pay any amount you wish, sir.

268
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:34,149
And what if I wish
to pay zero?

269
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:35,775
(chuckles)
Well, it's up to you.

270
00:11:35,861 --> 00:11:37,951
Ooh, so it's up
to me, is it?

271
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:39,740
-Yes.
-I see.

272
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:43,874
And you think that people
are gonna pay you $4.50

273
00:11:43,953 --> 00:11:45,413
even though
they don't have to

274
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:47,076
just out of the goodness
of their--

275
00:11:47,164 --> 00:11:50,544
(laughing)
Well, anything you say.

276
00:11:50,626 --> 00:11:51,956
Good luck, lady.

277
00:11:52,044 --> 00:11:53,134
You're going to need it.

278
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:55,672
-Mr. Bergstrom!
-Hi, Lisa.

279
00:11:55,756 --> 00:11:58,046
Hey! you don't have to pay.
Read the sign.

280
00:11:58,134 --> 00:12:00,764
-And this must be your father.
-(sighs)

281
00:12:00,845 --> 00:12:03,505
His teeth had jagged edges
to rip through your body,

282
00:12:03,597 --> 00:12:05,347
but he could've
swallowed you whole.

283
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:07,733
-Wow!
-Actually, Mr. Simpson,

284
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:10,730
they do know a great deal about
the process of mummification.

285
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:13,573
First they pulled the brain out
through the nose with an iron hook.

286
00:12:13,649 --> 00:12:15,319
then stuffed the insides
with sawdust and onions.

287
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:18,201
{\an8}-Eww! Gross!
-Ooh! Pretty creepy.

288
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:20,699
Still, I'd rather have him
chasing me than The Wolfman.

289
00:12:20,781 --> 00:12:22,121
Oh, Lord.

290
00:12:30,082 --> 00:12:31,962
Mr. Simpson, I am going
to be presumptuous.

291
00:12:32,042 --> 00:12:33,882
I have noticed
that Lisa seems to feel

292
00:12:33,961 --> 00:12:35,801
she has no strong
male role model.

293
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,670
-She said that?
-Well, no, she didn't say it,

294
00:12:38,758 --> 00:12:40,968
-but, you know, she--
-But you can tell, right?

295
00:12:41,051 --> 00:12:43,971
She looks around and sees everybody
else's dad with a good education,

296
00:12:44,054 --> 00:12:46,064
youthful looks,
and a clean credit record

297
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:48,520
and thinks, "Why me?
What did I do to deserve

298
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,271
-this fat, old piece of--
-Mr. Simpson,

299
00:12:50,352 --> 00:12:51,982
you have got to be
a bigger man.

300
00:12:52,062 --> 00:12:54,402
There is a wonderful girl's
future at stake.

301
00:12:54,482 --> 00:12:56,442
Well, if she's so wonderful,
give her an "A."

302
00:12:56,525 --> 00:12:57,775
I am giving her an "A."

303
00:12:57,860 --> 00:12:59,950
Great, but don't tell her it was
a favor to me. Tell her she earned it.

304
00:13:00,029 --> 00:13:01,819
Mr. Simpson, she did earn it!

305
00:13:01,906 --> 00:13:04,776
You are smooth.
I'll give you that.

306
00:13:08,746 --> 00:13:10,956
He ruined the one chance
I had of getting

307
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:13,630
to know Mr. Bergstrom
outside of school.

308
00:13:13,709 --> 00:13:16,129
Well, I'll tell you what.

309
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:18,212
Why don't we invite
Mr. Bergstrom to dinner?

310
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:20,667
Oh, Mom, that's wonderful!

311
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:21,878
Can I find out
his favorite dish

312
00:13:21,967 --> 00:13:23,177
-and help you make it?
-Sure!

313
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:24,430
-Can I wear your jewelry?
-Sure!

314
00:13:24,512 --> 00:13:25,512
-Can I get my ears pierced?
-No.

315
00:13:25,596 --> 00:13:26,716
-Can I dye my shoes pink?
-Yes.

316
00:13:26,806 --> 00:13:27,926
-Can I paint my nails?
-No.

317
00:13:28,015 --> 00:13:30,225
-Can we have wine? Can I have wine?
-Yes. No.

318
00:13:30,309 --> 00:13:31,389
- Does Bart have to be there?
- Yes.

319
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:33,017
Can we do it this week?

320
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:35,363
"Mr. Bergstrom,
May we request the pleasure

321
00:13:35,439 --> 00:13:37,729
of your company..."
No.

322
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:39,397
"Mr. Bergstrom, if you're
not doing anything

323
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:41,275
this Friday..." No.

324
00:13:41,362 --> 00:13:43,742
"Mr. Bergstrom,
Do you like pork chops?"

325
00:13:43,823 --> 00:13:46,123
Oh, no,
of course you wouldn't.

326
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:48,541
(gasps)

327
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:51,159
Good morning, Lisa.
I'm back.

328
00:13:57,127 --> 00:14:00,047
You see, class, my lyme
disease turned out to be...

329
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:02,760
ahem, psy-cho-somatic.

330
00:14:02,842 --> 00:14:04,262
Does that mean you're crazy?

331
00:14:04,343 --> 00:14:05,763
No, that means
she was faking it.

332
00:14:05,845 --> 00:14:07,675
No, actually,
it was a little of both.

333
00:14:07,763 --> 00:14:10,473
Sometimes, when a disease
is in all the magazines

334
00:14:10,558 --> 00:14:12,178
and on all the news shows,

335
00:14:12,268 --> 00:14:14,518
it's only natural
that you think you have it.

336
00:14:14,603 --> 00:14:16,733
-Where's Mr. Bergstrom?
-I don't know.

337
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:19,074
Although I'd sure like
to talk to him.

338
00:14:19,149 --> 00:14:22,949
He didn't touch my lesson plan.
What did he teach you?

339
00:14:23,028 --> 00:14:25,278
That life is worth living.
(gasps)

340
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:27,074
(crying)

341
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:29,787
The polls will be open from
now until the end of recess.

342
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:33,959
Now, just in case any of you have
decided to put any thought into this,

343
00:14:34,039 --> 00:14:36,129
we'll have our
final statements.

344
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:37,208
Martin?

345
00:14:37,293 --> 00:14:40,343
I don't think there's
anything left to say.

346
00:14:40,421 --> 00:14:42,381
-Bart?
-Victory party under the slide!

347
00:14:42,464 --> 00:14:44,384
(cheering)

348
00:14:45,843 --> 00:14:47,603
(buzzing)

349
00:14:47,678 --> 00:14:50,428
{\an8}Mr. Bergstrom!

350
00:14:50,514 --> 00:14:52,144
{\an8}Mr. Bergstrom!

351
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:54,484
Hey! Hey!
He moved out this morning.

352
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:57,310
He must have a new job--
He took his Copernicus costume.

353
00:14:57,396 --> 00:14:59,396
Do you know where
I can find him?

354
00:14:59,481 --> 00:15:01,821
Uh, I think he's taking
the next train to Capital City.

355
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:04,191
The train, how like him.

356
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:06,988
Traditional,
yet environmentally sound.

357
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:09,662
Yes, and it's been
the backbone of our country

358
00:15:09,742 --> 00:15:13,952
since Leland Stanford drove that
golden spike at Promontory Point.

359
00:15:14,038 --> 00:15:17,288
-I see he touched you too.
-(both sigh)

360
00:15:17,374 --> 00:15:20,634
-Thanks for your vote, man.
-I didn't vote. Voting's for geeks.

361
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:22,591
Well, you got that right.

362
00:15:22,671 --> 00:15:24,471
Thanks for your vote, girls.

363
00:15:24,548 --> 00:15:25,838
BOTH: We forgot.

364
00:15:25,925 --> 00:15:27,045
Well, don't sweat it.

365
00:15:27,134 --> 00:15:28,184
Just so long as a couple
of people did.

366
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,680
-Right, Milhouse?
-Uh-uh.

367
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:31,262
-Lewis?
-No.

368
00:15:31,347 --> 00:15:33,847
-Somebody must have voted.
-What about you, Bart?

369
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:36,273
-Didn't you vote?
-Uh-oh.

370
00:15:36,352 --> 00:15:39,062
-(school bell)
-(screaming)

371
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:42,516
(cheering)

372
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:44,818
I demand a recount.

373
00:15:44,902 --> 00:15:46,702
One for Martin.
Two for Martin.

374
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:48,819
-Would you like another recount?
-No.

375
00:15:48,906 --> 00:15:50,776
Well, I just wanna make sure.

376
00:15:50,866 --> 00:15:54,656
One for Martin. Two for Martin.
(chuckles)

377
00:15:54,745 --> 00:15:55,655
This way, Mr. President.

378
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:02,461
MAN (on P.A.):
<i>Now boarding on track five...</i>

379
00:16:02,544 --> 00:16:04,424
Mr. Bergstrom!

380
00:16:04,505 --> 00:16:06,085
Hey, Mr. Bergstrom!

381
00:16:06,173 --> 00:16:08,513
Hey! Lisa!

382
00:16:08,592 --> 00:16:10,342
Hey, Lisa, indeed.

383
00:16:10,427 --> 00:16:12,547
What? What is it?

384
00:16:12,638 --> 00:16:14,678
Oh, I mean...

385
00:16:14,765 --> 00:16:17,685
Were you just going to
leave, just like that?

386
00:16:17,768 --> 00:16:19,518
Aw, I'm sorry, Lisa.

387
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:22,773
You know, it's the life
of the substitute teacher.

388
00:16:22,856 --> 00:16:24,016
He's a fraud.

389
00:16:24,108 --> 00:16:25,938
Today he might be
wearing gym shorts,

390
00:16:26,026 --> 00:16:29,196
tomorrow he's speaking
French or pretending

391
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:30,949
to know how to run a band saw,

392
00:16:31,031 --> 00:16:33,201
-or God knows what.
-You can't go.

393
00:16:33,283 --> 00:16:35,203
You're the best teacher
I'll ever have.

394
00:16:35,285 --> 00:16:37,705
Aw, that's not true.
Other teachers will come along.

395
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:40,868
-Oh, please!
-No, I can't lie to you, I am the best,

396
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:43,708
but, you know, they need me over
in the projects of Capital City.

397
00:16:43,794 --> 00:16:46,174
(nearly whispering)
But I need you too.

398
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:49,125
That's the problem
with being middle class.

399
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:50,796
Anybody who really cares
will abandon you

400
00:16:50,884 --> 00:16:52,054
for those who need it more.

401
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:56,096
I... I understand.

402
00:16:56,181 --> 00:17:00,351
Mr. Bergstrom,
I'm going to miss you.

403
00:17:01,645 --> 00:17:03,435
I'll tell you what.

404
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:06,442
Whenever you feel
like you're alone

405
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:08,645
and there's nobody
you can rely on,

406
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:11,356
this is all you need to know.

407
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:13,567
Thank you, Mr. Bergstrom.

408
00:17:13,657 --> 00:17:14,697
MAN: All aboard!

409
00:17:14,783 --> 00:17:17,243
So, I guess this is it.

410
00:17:17,327 --> 00:17:19,117
If you don't mind,

411
00:17:19,204 --> 00:17:22,004
I'll just run alongside
the train

412
00:17:22,082 --> 00:17:24,422
as it speeds you
from my life.

413
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:38,142
Good-bye, Lisa honey.

414
00:17:38,223 --> 00:17:42,733
It'll be okay.
Just read the note!

415
00:17:42,811 --> 00:17:44,611
(train whistle blows)

416
00:17:49,109 --> 00:17:51,359
HOMER:
Bart didn't get one vote?

417
00:17:51,445 --> 00:17:54,815
Oh, this is the worst thing
that could ever happen to us.

418
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:56,327
All right, all right,

419
00:17:56,408 --> 00:17:58,198
spilt milk, spilt milk,
spilt milk.

420
00:17:58,285 --> 00:18:00,495
-What are you so mopey about?
-Nothing.

421
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:02,749
Lisa, tell your father.

422
00:18:02,831 --> 00:18:04,791
Mr. Bergstrom
left today.

423
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:07,335
-Oh?
-He's gone forever.

424
00:18:07,419 --> 00:18:10,169
-And?
-I didn't think you'd understand.

425
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:14,965
Hey! Just because I don't
care doesn't mean I don't understand.

426
00:18:15,052 --> 00:18:17,762
I'm glad I'm not crying,

427
00:18:17,846 --> 00:18:19,426
because I would hate
for you to think

428
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:23,055
that what I'm about to say
is based on emotion.

429
00:18:23,143 --> 00:18:25,443
-But you, sir--
-Huh?

430
00:18:25,521 --> 00:18:28,191
-...are a baboon!
-(gasps) Me?

431
00:18:28,273 --> 00:18:31,283
Yes, you! Baboon! Baboon!
Baboon! Baboon!

432
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:33,860
I don't think you realize
what you're saying.

433
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:36,116
(screaming)
Baboon!

434
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:38,778
-(crying)
-Whoa.

435
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:40,447
Somebody was bound
to say it one day.

436
00:18:40,536 --> 00:18:41,406
I just can't believe
it was her.

437
00:18:41,495 --> 00:18:43,075
Did you hear that, Marge?

438
00:18:43,163 --> 00:18:45,333
She called me a baboon!

439
00:18:45,415 --> 00:18:48,625
The stupidest, ugliest,
smelliest ape of them all.

440
00:18:48,710 --> 00:18:51,590
Homer, you're not allowed to have
hurt feelings right now.

441
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:53,972
There's a little girl upstairs
who needs you.

442
00:18:54,049 --> 00:18:56,299
Her confidence
in her father is shaken,

443
00:18:56,385 --> 00:18:59,805
and no little girl can be happy
unless she has faith in her daddy.

444
00:18:59,888 --> 00:19:01,888
(groans)

445
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:04,814
Oh.

446
00:19:04,893 --> 00:19:07,733
(reading)
"Go away."

447
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:09,063
(sobbing)

448
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:12,108
Lisa, don't hold
anything back.

449
00:19:12,192 --> 00:19:14,112
You can tell me.

450
00:19:14,194 --> 00:19:17,574
Are you crying because
you called Daddy a baboon?

451
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:19,316
-No!
-Nuts.

452
00:19:19,408 --> 00:19:20,908
D'oh!

453
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:24,253
-This isn't going well at all.
-Look!

454
00:19:24,329 --> 00:19:26,579
-If you just want me to forgive you--
-No, no, no.

455
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:28,915
I just wish
I knew what to say.

456
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:31,381
(melancholy music playing)

457
00:19:31,461 --> 00:19:34,011
Although,
maybe this music will help.

458
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:37,429
Now, you lost someone
special, and it hurts.

459
00:19:37,509 --> 00:19:41,049
I'm lucky, because I never
lost anyone special to me.

460
00:19:41,138 --> 00:19:44,098
Everyone special to me
is under this roof.

461
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:46,023
-Oh...
-It's true.

462
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:49,981
Now, you'll have lots of special people
in your life, Lisa.

463
00:19:50,063 --> 00:19:53,153
There's probably someplace
where they all get together,

464
00:19:53,233 --> 00:19:56,703
and the food is real good,
and guys like me are serving drinks.

465
00:19:56,778 --> 00:20:01,158
Oh, well, maybe
I can't explain all this,

466
00:20:01,241 --> 00:20:03,201
but I can fix
your dollhouse for you.

467
00:20:03,285 --> 00:20:06,705
At least I'm good
at monkey work.

468
00:20:06,788 --> 00:20:08,578
You know? Monkey?

469
00:20:08,665 --> 00:20:10,825
{\an8}-You know what I mean?
-Yeah.

470
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:12,998
{\an8}Bet I can hold these nails
in place with my tail.

471
00:20:13,086 --> 00:20:16,466
-(both chuckle)
-(imitating monkey)

472
00:20:16,548 --> 00:20:19,178
(laughing)

473
00:20:19,259 --> 00:20:20,679
You're so silly.

474
00:20:20,761 --> 00:20:23,721
-Give me a banana.
-I don't have any bananas.

475
00:20:23,805 --> 00:20:25,635
Come on, you're
holding out on me.

476
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:27,774
(both laughing)

477
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:32,690
I'm sorry I called you
a baboon, Dad.

478
00:20:32,773 --> 00:20:34,073
Think nothing of it.

479
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:38,403
BART: President prince,
president princess,

480
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:39,857
president priss...

481
00:20:41,365 --> 00:20:44,075
Hey, what's the matter, son?

482
00:20:44,159 --> 00:20:45,739
Aw, Dad...

483
00:20:45,827 --> 00:20:48,907
If just me, Milhouse,
and Louis had voted.

